{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"sealable container","id":"r119888","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-X1Kq3afJFU4\/XZad-PT9osI\/AAAAAAAAghc\/QQjgfbZZhr0IMeP8FFrINQ-Ci4mvzmziwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Nb_ZUethBMx-BylC.png","title":"Spicy peach and mango chutney","publishedAt":"2017-01-22T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"500 g water"},{"content":"500 g peaches"},{"content":"20 g piece fresh ginger, peeled"},{"content":"1 tsp sichuan peppercorns"},{"content":"1 tsp dried chilli flakes"},{"content":"2 star anise"},{"content":"1 cinnamon quill"},{"content":"100 g fresh mango, flesh only"},{"content":"200 g raw sugar"},{"content":"1 tsp ground ginger"},{"content":"40 g Shaoxing wine"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"7.2 g","fat":"1.9 g","uom":"per 1 total recipe","carbohydrates":"261.2 g","calories":"4625 kJ \/ 1101 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Place water into mixing bowl. Using a sharp knife, make a small slit into the skin of each peach. Place peaches into Varoma dish, place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Allow peaches to cool, then remove and discard skins. Discard peach pits and set peach flesh aside. Rinse and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place ginger, peppercorns and chilli flakes into mixing bowl and chop <b>15 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add star anise, cinnamon quill, mango, sugar, ground ginger and reserved peach flesh and cook <b>20 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>, then blend <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>, until peaches have broken down."},{"content":"Add Shaoxing wine and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer into a container and set aside to cool. Remove whole spices, if desired, before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Tinned peaches and mangoes can be used in this recipe. They will not need to be steamed and can hold more liquid so you may need to cook the glaze a little longer (an extra <strong>5 min\/100°C\/speed <\/strong>) in step 3. Check the texture of your fruit; you may not need to blend it in step 4 if it's broken down quite a bit.","This chutney is lovely with chicken wings, lamb ribs and ham. You can also use it as a glaze when baking ham.","Store in sterilised jars to preserve it, or store in a sealable container in the refrigerator for up to 3 weeks."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","45m","1 total recipe"]}